title: Grateful Dead Live at Alligator Alley Gymnasium, U of Florida on 1980-11-29
venue: Alligator Alley Gymnasium, U of Florida
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Promised Land, Candyman, Minglewood Blues, Row Jimmy, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Althea-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Don't Ease Me In

Set 2

Shakedown Street-> Franklin's Tower-> Estimated Prophet-> He's Gone-> Truckin'-> Drums-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Good Lovin', E: Casey Jones

reviews.review_text: Beyer + 80-81 = Sweeeet Killer show as discussed ad nauseum.  I don't know where the board walked off to, but with recordings like this who needs it?  This source is my favorite.  The Beyer 88s provide a warm sound that fits with the GD tones and rooms of '80-81 perfectly.  Many other Auds of this period benefit greatly from them as well.  Love it.
Agreed - best source for this show. Props to "Mad River Rich" for the recording.
Definitely in the sweet spot This would be the B spot in the split spot somewhere at the Y near the sweet spot this sounds damn good 5 stars who needs a board

Gainesville Green Awesome show and great one to revisit! Alligator Alley 80 circulated widely back in the day. I too had a copy on a TDK! (See Wise Copy).
Quite possibly the best Other One with Brent...

Nice show! I was intrigued by Bob's "game" comments just prior to the encore, so I did some searching; it seems the U of Florida Gators had hosted the University of Miami earlier in the day... and lost, 31-7.
I always find it amusing when the boys made in-show comments on things like this~
